<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,256,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new subspecies (
<figureCitation box="[567,666,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,202,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: adults. 1, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, male, Russian Altai, Aktash (ZISP); 2, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (AVB); 3, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 4, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 5, X. a. candelarum, male, Germany, Dresden (ZSM); 6, X. a. candelarum, male, NE Kazakhstan, Dmitrievka (AVB); 7, X. a. candelarum, Mongolia, male, Töv aimak (PGM); 8, X. a. ashworthii, male, Great Britain, Wales (ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264712/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs 
<number box="[626,666,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
) differs externally from 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1234,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[947,1234,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. ashworthii candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1253,1352,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,202,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: adults. 1, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, male, Russian Altai, Aktash (ZISP); 2, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (AVB); 3, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 4, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 5, X. a. candelarum, male, Germany, Dresden (ZSM); 6, X. a. candelarum, male, NE Kazakhstan, Dmitrievka (AVB); 7, X. a. candelarum, Mongolia, male, Töv aimak (PGM); 8, X. a. ashworthii, male, Great Britain, Wales (ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264712/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs 
<number box="[1311,1352,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
</figureCitation>
) in the narrower forewing (like 
<emphasis box="[428,615,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
X. a. 
<taxonomicName box="[495,612,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ashworthii">ashworthii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[627,694,602,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,202,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: adults. 1, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, male, Russian Altai, Aktash (ZISP); 2, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (AVB); 3, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 4, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 5, X. a. candelarum, male, Germany, Dresden (ZSM); 6, X. a. candelarum, male, NE Kazakhstan, Dmitrievka (AVB); 7, X. a. candelarum, Mongolia, male, Töv aimak (PGM); 8, X. a. ashworthii, male, Great Britain, Wales (ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264712/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[681,694,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) having darker ground colour without brown suffusion. The new subspecies differs clearly from 
<taxonomicName box="[484,666,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[484,666,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the female genitalia structure: in 
<taxonomicName box="[1050,1256,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[1050,1256,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1269,1388,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs 
<number box="[1323,1388,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="11.12">11, 12</number>
</figureCitation>
) the posterior sclerotised part of the ductus bursae is longer and narrower than in 
<taxonomicName box="[974,1158,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[974,1158,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1174,1252,672,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[1224,1252,672,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
), the antevaginal plate is narrower and more or less V-shaped (in 
<taxonomicName box="[679,866,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[679,866,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antevaginal plate is more or less U-shaped), the corpus bursae is somewhat smaller. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[788,998,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[788,998,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1014,1080,741,764]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[1066,1080,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) are very close to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[293,371,776,799]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[344,371,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) and differ only in the somewhat longer and narrower pollex and the much larger apical process of the juxta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,256,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Molecular data.</emphasis>
Two specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[596,806,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[596,806,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from different isolated localities of Central Altai (Aktash vill. and Chulyshman valley) were compared with two specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[895,1080,879,903]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[895,1080,879,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe (
<collectingCountry box="[1240,1369,880,903]" name="Switzerland" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
Alps) and Northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[341,465,914,937]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[481,561,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,191,1847]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Xestia ashworthii: barcoding tree, distribution map and habitat. 14, Diagram of DNA barcoding tree for Xestia ashworthii sspp. and X. wockei; 15, Distribution map of X. a. centralaltaica and X. a. candelarum in southern Siberia; 16, Russia, Altai Republic, Ulagan district, Chulyshman valley, 51 º 00 ' N, 88 º 01 ' E, the habitat of X. a. centralaltaica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264714/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[531,561,914,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). The comparison was made also with sequences of other 
<taxonomicName box="[1187,1302,914,937]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Megasema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1187,1302,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Megasema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species free available on the 
<collectionCode box="[336,409,949,972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">BOLD</collectionCode>
Systems website (www.boldsystems.org). Distance between a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1246,1435,948,972]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[1246,1435,948,972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[214,341,984,1007]" name="Switzerland" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
Alps and a specimen from NE 
<collectingCountry box="[708,832,984,1007]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
is 0.17 %. Distance between two specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in two isolated localities also is 0.17 %. Minimal distance between specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NE 
<collectingCountry box="[336,462,1053,1076]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Aktash" authorityName="Aktash" box="[521,827,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[521,727,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
(Aktash)
</taxonomicName>
is 0.52 %. Maximal distance between specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[292,422,1088,1111]" name="Switzerland" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[483,690,1087,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[483,690,1087,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chulyshman valley) is 0.87 %. Distance between the two specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[184,377,1121,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="candelarum">
<emphasis box="[184,377,1121,1145]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. candelarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and specimens of a closely related species 
<taxonomicName box="[878,986,1121,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wockei">
<emphasis box="[878,986,1121,1145]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. wockei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(samples from 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1247,1122,1145]" name="Canada" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Canada</collectingCountry>
with incomplete sequences 
<number box="[266,306,1157,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="609.0">609</number>
and 
<number box="[357,397,1157,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="641.0">641</number>
bp) is 1.75 % (
<figureCitation box="[560,639,1157,1180]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,191,1847]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Xestia ashworthii: barcoding tree, distribution map and habitat. 14, Diagram of DNA barcoding tree for Xestia ashworthii sspp. and X. wockei; 15, Distribution map of X. a. centralaltaica and X. a. candelarum in southern Siberia; 16, Russia, Altai Republic, Ulagan district, Chulyshman valley, 51 º 00 ' N, 88 º 01 ' E, the habitat of X. a. centralaltaica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264714/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[610,639,1157,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,256,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,1192,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[431,532,1192,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,202,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: adults. 1, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, male, Russian Altai, Aktash (ZISP); 2, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (AVB); 3, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 4, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, female, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley (MDS); 5, X. a. candelarum, male, Germany, Dresden (ZSM); 6, X. a. candelarum, male, NE Kazakhstan, Dmitrievka (AVB); 7, X. a. candelarum, Mongolia, male, Töv aimak (PGM); 8, X. a. ashworthii, male, Great Britain, Wales (ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264712/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs 
<number box="[489,532,1192,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[672,794,1192,1215]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" unit="mm" value="40.0" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="39.0">39–41 mm</quantity>
. Antennae ciliate in males and filiform in females. Head, thorax and abdomen dark ashy grey. Ground colour of forewing monotonous dark ashy grey. Subbasal line thin, blackish, dentate; antemedial line thin, blackish, irregularly dentate, with large dark spot on the costa; postmedial line dentate, with large dark spot on the costa; subterminal line dark, strongly diffuse; terminal line thin, dark grey, wavy. Orbicular and reniform stigmata somewhat paler than ground colour, cell between them dark grey. Cilia dark ashy grey. Hindwing ashy grey, somewhat paler basally. Discal spot semilunar, dark grey, strongly diffuse. Cilia grey. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1170,1336,1365,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1354,1423,1365,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[1407,1423,1365,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, narrow, curved, apically pointed; tegumen short, penicular lobes broad; vinculum short, U-shaped. Juxta narrow, hearth-like, its apical process very large, lobe-like. Valva elongated, basally broadened, slightly curved, its apical part narrowed, rounded, strongly setose; pollex long, narrow; harpe relatively long, trigonal slightly curved, apically rounded; sacculus broad. Aedeagus moderately long, broad, carina ventrally armed with a pointed spine; vesica tubular, curved dorsally, with large, sack-like dorsal subbasal diverticulum, bulbous medio-lateral diverticulum and dorsal sclerotised band. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[337,525,1573,1596]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[539,662,1573,1596]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,199,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[155,1432,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Xestia ashworthii sspp.: male (9, 10) and female (11 – 13) genitalia. 9, X. a. centralaltaica, holotype, Russian Altai, Aktash, slide AV 0399 Volynkin; 10, X. a. candelarum, West Siberian Plain, Novosibirsk reg., slide AV 0748 Volynkin; 11, X. a. centralaltaica, paratype, Russian Altai, Chulyshman valley, slide AV 0360 Volynkin; 12, ditto, slide AV 1755 Volynkin; 13, X. a. candelarum, East Siberia, Minusinsk, slide AV 0011 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Figs 
<number box="[593,662,1573,1596]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="11.12">11, 12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short, conical. Apophyses posteriores long, thin; apophyses anteriores about half as shorter, thin. Antevaginal plate large, strongly sclerotised, horseshoe-like. Posterior part of ductus bursae strongly sclerotised, broad, moderately long; anterior part of ductus bursae about half as shorter, membranous, with a very small membranous lateral pouch. Corpus bursae very broad, sack-like, slightly wrinkledsclerotised; appendix bursae large, sack-like, distally broadened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,256,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,519,1746,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
The new subspecies is known from Central Altai province of the Russian Altai Mts. (Volynkin 
<number box="[265,320,1781,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="2012.0">2012</number>
) (
<figureCitation box="[344,424,1781,1804]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,191,1847]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Xestia ashworthii: barcoding tree, distribution map and habitat. 14, Diagram of DNA barcoding tree for Xestia ashworthii sspp. and X. wockei; 15, Distribution map of X. a. centralaltaica and X. a. candelarum in southern Siberia; 16, Russia, Altai Republic, Ulagan district, Chulyshman valley, 51 º 00 ' N, 88 º 01 ' E, the habitat of X. a. centralaltaica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264714/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[395,424,1781,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[446,655,1780,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ashworthii" subSpecies="centralaltaica">
<emphasis box="[446,655,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">X. a. centralaltaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits rocky slopes and steppe valleys at medium high altitudes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,258,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,191,1847]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Xestia ashworthii: barcoding tree, distribution map and habitat. 14, Diagram of DNA barcoding tree for Xestia ashworthii sspp. and X. wockei; 15, Distribution map of X. a. centralaltaica and X. a. candelarum in southern Siberia; 16, Russia, Altai Republic, Ulagan district, Chulyshman valley, 51 º 00 ' N, 88 º 01 ' E, the habitat of X. a. centralaltaica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264714/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1816,1839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
), the moths fly from late June to mid July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
